            <h2>jQuery</h2>
            <p>

                jQuery is a fast, small, and feature-rich JavaScript library. It makes things like HTML document traversal and manipulation, event handling, animation, and Ajax much simpler with an easy-to-use API that works across a multitude of browsers. jQuery was originally created by John Resig and first released in January 2006.
                This site uses jQuery in <code>colors.js</code> to change the page colors for the night/day theme toggle, for example:
                <ul>
                    <li><code>$('a').css('color', color)</code> &mdash; change the color of all links</li>
                    <li><code>$('body').css('backgroundColor', color)</code> &mdash; change the background color</li>
                </ul>

            </p>
